1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:06,530
[opening music theme]

2
00:00:16,850 --> 00:00:19,114
<i>( male narrator)</i>
<i>Since the very beginning</i>

3
00:00:19,186 --> 00:00:22,849
<i>my ancestors have known</i>
<i>of a giant creature.</i>

4
00:00:22,923 --> 00:00:27,451
<i>A man like beast</i>
<i>they call Taku He.</i>

5
00:00:27,527 --> 00:00:33,295
<i>Like us, Taku He hunted,</i>
<i>fished, and raised his young,</i>

6
00:00:33,366 --> 00:00:35,994
<i>taking only what he needed.</i>

7
00:00:36,069 --> 00:00:40,472
<i>But when the white man came</i>
<i>blasting the mountain for gold</i>

8
00:00:40,540 --> 00:00:43,600
<i>killing many animals,</i>
<i>everything changed.</i>

9
00:00:45,111 --> 00:00:50,811
<i>Taku He were deeply angry</i>
<i>and many died by his rage.</i>

10
00:00:50,884 --> 00:00:52,647
<i>In revenge,</i>

11
00:00:52,719 --> 00:00:56,052
<i>the white men spilled</i>
<i>the innocent blood</i>
<i>of my people.</i>

12
00:00:56,122 --> 00:01:00,252
<i>It was a time</i>
<i>of great sorrow and hatred.</i>

13
00:01:02,862 --> 00:01:06,525
<i>Even today,</i>
<i>when mountain spirits</i>
<i>claim a life,</i>

14
00:01:06,600 --> 00:01:10,092
<i>it is we</i>
<i>who are held in contempt.</i>

15
00:01:12,105 --> 00:01:15,734
<i>There are even those</i>
<i>who wish us dead.</i>

16
00:01:16,977 --> 00:01:19,036
[bang]

17
00:01:24,684 --> 00:01:26,379
What the hell
are you shooting at?

18
00:01:26,453 --> 00:01:28,512
I've seen somethin'
over there.

19
00:01:30,890 --> 00:01:32,687
[bang]

20
00:01:32,759 --> 00:01:36,718
Now, that's how you kill
a tree stump.

21
00:01:36,796 --> 00:01:39,731
You idiots
are scared of a creature
off in the woods.

22
00:01:39,799 --> 00:01:42,563
In case you don't remember,
we're here to kill a bear.

23
00:01:42,636 --> 00:01:46,094
Spread out. We only got
a couple of hours
of day light left.

24
00:01:46,172 --> 00:01:48,072
[shouting]
Spread out!

25
00:01:51,278 --> 00:01:54,441
[mystery music]

26
00:02:22,776 --> 00:02:25,370
[low grunt]

27
00:02:48,535 --> 00:02:51,197
[man shouts]

28
00:03:02,749 --> 00:03:04,410
[grunt]

29
00:03:18,064 --> 00:03:20,965
[grunt]

30
00:03:21,034 --> 00:03:22,194
What the hell?

31
00:03:22,268 --> 00:03:24,998
[grunting]

32
00:03:40,887 --> 00:03:43,617
[soft music]

33
00:04:09,182 --> 00:04:11,582
Jimbo!

34
00:04:11,651 --> 00:04:13,084
Colonel!

35
00:04:33,206 --> 00:04:35,231
[smells]

36
00:04:52,392 --> 00:04:55,327
[thriller music]

37
00:05:00,667 --> 00:05:01,656
Jimbo.

38
00:05:05,104 --> 00:05:07,834
[thriller music]

39
00:05:27,660 --> 00:05:31,152
[alarm clock goes off]

40
00:05:31,231 --> 00:05:33,699
[ringing]

41
00:05:36,069 --> 00:05:37,798
[ringing stops]

42
00:05:43,243 --> 00:05:44,471
Mom.

43
00:05:46,913 --> 00:05:50,610
<i>( mother)</i>
<i>l must've dozed off.</i>
<i>Let me make you something.</i>

44
00:05:50,683 --> 00:05:52,548
No, not much wanting
for this first period.

45
00:05:52,619 --> 00:05:53,711
Oh, no.

46
00:05:53,786 --> 00:05:56,914
Okay.
Bye, mom.

47
00:05:56,990 --> 00:05:58,389
Oh!
Your dad called.

48
00:05:58,458 --> 00:06:00,983
He wants you to spend
spring break in his place.

49
00:06:01,060 --> 00:06:02,994
I can't.

50
00:06:04,163 --> 00:06:06,427
You can't punish him
forever, you know.

51
00:06:06,499 --> 00:06:10,401
[soft music]

52
00:07:30,883 --> 00:07:34,284
[bell rings]

53
00:07:34,354 --> 00:07:37,414
<i>[Vancamp]</i>
<i>As we all know, next week</i>
<i>is spring break week.</i>

54
00:07:37,523 --> 00:07:39,423
[all cheer]

55
00:07:39,492 --> 00:07:41,858
Your endangered
species projects are due

56
00:07:41,928 --> 00:07:43,361
the Monday we return.

57
00:07:43,429 --> 00:07:44,691
[all sigh]

58
00:07:44,764 --> 00:07:48,222
I don't make up the curricula.
I just enforce it.

59
00:07:48,301 --> 00:07:51,862
Now, for those
professional procrastinators
among us

60
00:07:51,938 --> 00:07:53,667
who have yet
to select the topic,

61
00:07:53,740 --> 00:07:55,640
just remember,

62
00:07:57,043 --> 00:07:59,204
Seeing as that you
already know all of this,

63
00:07:59,278 --> 00:08:04,409
perhaps you'd like to give us
an example of an endangered
species, Mr. Kelter.

64
00:08:04,484 --> 00:08:05,781
[Vancamp]
Mr. Kelter.

65
00:08:05,852 --> 00:08:07,217
[murmuring]

66
00:08:07,286 --> 00:08:08,344
Mr. Kelter!

67
00:08:08,421 --> 00:08:11,083
Uhm, uh... Shea.

68
00:08:11,157 --> 00:08:13,057
(Jay )
Definitely Shea.

69
00:08:13,126 --> 00:08:14,821
Did you hear the question?

70
00:08:14,894 --> 00:08:17,988
Yeah. You were talking about
endangered species.

71
00:08:18,064 --> 00:08:20,760
It just kinda looks to me
like pretty girls around here

72
00:08:20,833 --> 00:08:23,165
are becoming
an endangered species.

73
00:08:23,236 --> 00:08:26,797
After class, Kelter,
will discuss
your endangered grade.

74
00:08:26,873 --> 00:08:31,003
Mr. Winslow,
perhaps you'd like
to help us out.

75
00:08:36,049 --> 00:08:37,141
Uh.

76
00:08:37,216 --> 00:08:41,482
Woodland caribou,
the gray wolf,

77
00:08:41,554 --> 00:08:44,455
short-tailed albatross,
brown pelican,

78
00:08:44,524 --> 00:08:49,018
white-tailed deer,
spidered owl,
leatherback sea turtle.

79
00:08:49,095 --> 00:08:52,758
Uh, sea otter,
grizzly bear.

80
00:08:52,832 --> 00:08:54,993
The Sasquatch.

81
00:08:55,068 --> 00:08:57,002
[all laugh]

82
00:08:57,070 --> 00:08:59,163
(Vancamp )
That's nine
out of then.

83
00:08:59,238 --> 00:09:02,674
Now, if you could just
duplicate that on a test.

84
00:09:02,742 --> 00:09:06,178
Why don't you join
Mr. Kelter and I after class?

85
00:09:06,245 --> 00:09:08,713
Mr. Vancamp,
did you hear?

86
00:09:08,781 --> 00:09:12,239
A bunch of guys got killed
by a huge grizzly bear
up in Echo Mountain.

87
00:09:12,318 --> 00:09:13,979
(Vancamp )
A bunch of guys!

88
00:09:14,053 --> 00:09:17,284
Yeah, like ten or something.
They said it was really bad.
Totally sick.

89
00:09:17,356 --> 00:09:19,688
[bell rings]

90
00:09:19,759 --> 00:09:21,989
(Vancamp )
Well, there you have it.

91
00:09:22,061 --> 00:09:24,552
Well, enjoy your spring break

92
00:09:24,630 --> 00:09:28,430
and please, please,
whatever you do,
stay away from killer bears.

93
00:09:28,501 --> 00:09:30,196
Jay!

94
00:09:30,269 --> 00:09:32,737
Sorry.
I almost forgot.

95
00:09:32,805 --> 00:09:35,831
Just like you forgot
your homework
for the last three weeks.

96
00:09:35,908 --> 00:09:40,072
Listen, you're precariously close
to not passing this class.

97
00:09:40,146 --> 00:09:42,444
That means
you won't graduate.

98
00:09:42,515 --> 00:09:44,881
What are you talking about?
I have to graduate.

99
00:09:44,951 --> 00:09:50,253
Mr. Kelter, graduation is a privilege,
not a requirement.

100
00:09:50,323 --> 00:09:54,316
That's why I've decided
to team the both of you up.

101
00:09:54,393 --> 00:09:55,485
What? Why?

102
00:09:55,561 --> 00:09:57,153
You're joking, right?

103
00:09:57,230 --> 00:10:00,097
"He who helps others,
helps himself."

104
00:10:00,166 --> 00:10:01,895
I don't need his help.

105
00:10:01,968 --> 00:10:04,095
I can't help.

106
00:10:04,170 --> 00:10:06,832
Gentlemen, let me
put it to you in this light.

107
00:10:06,906 --> 00:10:11,172
If the two of you together

108
00:10:11,244 --> 00:10:15,681
don't produce an in-depth presentation
by Monday after next,

109
00:10:15,748 --> 00:10:18,046
one of you will be leaving
with an incomplete,

110
00:10:18,117 --> 00:10:21,143
and the other
won't be leaving at all.

111
00:10:23,222 --> 00:10:25,156
You didn't say
it was this bad.

112
00:10:27,226 --> 00:10:30,821
Bear attack?
Can't expect it to be pretty.

113
00:10:32,565 --> 00:10:34,294
Gotta get this
cleaned up.

114
00:10:34,367 --> 00:10:36,426
<i>You</i> have to get
this cleaned up, Sheriff.

115
00:10:36,502 --> 00:10:39,938
Tourists are gonna be up here
in a few weeks.

116
00:10:40,006 --> 00:10:43,601
It's all bull hairs.
That big motor is gonna drive
right past Pine Creek.

117
00:10:43,676 --> 00:10:46,543
They'll think
there's a killer bear
on the loose up here.

118
00:10:46,612 --> 00:10:48,842
We gotta control this
before it controls us.

119
00:10:48,915 --> 00:10:51,907
I've called the town meeting
for tonight.

120
00:10:51,984 --> 00:10:55,351
Calling meetings, Kassel?
Are you tr ying to give me another ulcer?

121
00:10:55,421 --> 00:10:57,013
That'll add fuel
to the fire!

122
00:10:57,089 --> 00:10:59,580
We cant let this get out.
Do you understand that?

123
00:10:59,659 --> 00:11:03,095
I understand that my job
is to protect the people of this town.

124
00:11:03,162 --> 00:11:06,461
They have the right to know
there's a pissed off predator out here.

125
00:11:06,532 --> 00:11:08,159
You don't know that, yet.

126
00:11:08,234 --> 00:11:11,897
If I read one word about this
in any paper but our own local dish rag,

127
00:11:11,971 --> 00:11:14,997
you're gonna have a tough time
finding work in Alaska.

128
00:11:15,074 --> 00:11:16,507
What's that, John?

129
00:11:18,377 --> 00:11:20,311
Nothing.

130
00:11:20,379 --> 00:11:24,076
Maybe all-knowing Indian
around here, Eagleheart.

131
00:11:24,150 --> 00:11:26,914
What do you think
we should do with this
vile creature?

132
00:11:26,986 --> 00:11:29,284
It's a noble savage.

133
00:11:29,355 --> 00:11:32,347
It's nice of you
to think so, Mayor,
but l'm just a ranger.

134
00:11:32,425 --> 00:11:35,861
Listen, we've contacted
the Federal Game Warden.

135
00:11:35,928 --> 00:11:38,897
He'll be here
with some tracking dogs
in a day or two.

136
00:11:38,965 --> 00:11:41,365
Until then,
Eagleheart and I
will try to find it.

137
00:11:41,434 --> 00:11:43,902
I don't give a rat's ass
who does it
or how you do it.

138
00:11:43,970 --> 00:11:46,939
You just make sure this thing
is last week's news.

139
00:11:50,810 --> 00:11:54,371
Johnson!
That way.

140
00:11:54,447 --> 00:11:58,349
Don't get too far ahead of us
or you'll be tomorrow's news.

141
00:12:01,687 --> 00:12:04,019
You don't really think
a bear did this, do you?

142
00:12:04,090 --> 00:12:06,183
You ever heard of a bear
killing three men?

143
00:12:07,460 --> 00:12:09,894
Well, it's what Janzer claims.

144
00:12:09,962 --> 00:12:12,658
Well, the poacher claims
it's a bear.

145
00:12:12,732 --> 00:12:15,496
Let's call it that.
It's probably better--

146
00:12:15,568 --> 00:12:17,559
Better than what?

147
00:12:17,637 --> 00:12:20,003
Listen, don't answer that.

148
00:12:20,072 --> 00:12:22,700
My only job
is to keep people happy.

149
00:12:22,775 --> 00:12:27,405
Unfortunately, those people
are gonna want blood for this.
You know that.

150
00:12:27,480 --> 00:12:31,883
I'm sure those yahoos
have wounded enough bears
to make that easy.

151
00:12:31,951 --> 00:12:34,920
Listen, I'll head
above the falls
and see what I can find.

152
00:12:34,987 --> 00:12:37,217
I give you two days.

153
00:12:37,290 --> 00:12:39,190
But take care of you, John.

154
00:12:39,258 --> 00:12:41,590
For God's sakes,
keep you radio on,
will you?

155
00:12:41,661 --> 00:12:44,926
I don't wanna have
to come back here
and rescue you, you noble ass.

156
00:12:50,403 --> 00:12:54,203
[rock music]

157
00:13:05,284 --> 00:13:07,411
[loud rock music]
[revs engine]

158
00:13:07,486 --> 00:13:11,149
[rock music continues]

159
00:13:16,128 --> 00:13:18,722
[tires screech]

160
00:13:21,100 --> 00:13:22,124
Jesus, man!

161
00:13:22,201 --> 00:13:23,361
What's up?

162
00:13:23,436 --> 00:13:25,597
That's a really nice bike
you got there.

163
00:13:25,671 --> 00:13:28,037
My sister's got a tutu
that'll match that real good.

164
00:13:28,107 --> 00:13:29,438
I hope it's pretty.

165
00:13:29,508 --> 00:13:32,033
Look, I ain't going back here
next year. Got that?

166
00:13:32,111 --> 00:13:33,669
You and I
don't like each other.

167
00:13:33,746 --> 00:13:35,373
We don't have
to like each other.

168
00:13:35,448 --> 00:13:37,279
We just have
to work together.

169
00:13:37,350 --> 00:13:41,081
Unless you get an incomplete,
I suggest you be
at the town meeting tonight.

170
00:13:41,153 --> 00:13:42,620
Why is that, Jay?

171
00:13:42,688 --> 00:13:45,680
Because you said yourself
bears are an endangered
species.

172
00:13:45,758 --> 00:13:47,521
It's grizzlies.

173
00:13:47,593 --> 00:13:49,561
Okay, whatever,
dick Britannica.

174
00:13:49,628 --> 00:13:51,061
Just be there, right?

175
00:13:52,531 --> 00:13:53,896
[tires screech]

176
00:13:53,966 --> 00:13:56,366
Oh, yeah.
By the way,

177
00:13:56,435 --> 00:14:00,030
my cousin Jenny,
she likes you.

178
00:14:00,106 --> 00:14:02,199
Don't ask me why.

179
00:14:02,274 --> 00:14:04,174
She's gonna be there
tonight, too.

180
00:14:04,243 --> 00:14:06,370
[tires screech]
[revs engine]

181
00:14:09,015 --> 00:14:12,746
[soft music]

182
00:14:41,781 --> 00:14:45,114
[low murmuring]

183
00:14:51,891 --> 00:14:55,019
Jenny, Richard.
Richard, Jenny.

184
00:14:55,094 --> 00:14:58,461
You're the one
that's coming with us
to the mountains this weekend.

185
00:14:58,531 --> 00:15:01,364
What? No.

186
00:15:01,434 --> 00:15:02,992
Jenny wants to come
along too,

187
00:15:03,069 --> 00:15:05,469
but I told her I didn't think
that was a good idea.

188
00:15:05,538 --> 00:15:06,766
That wouldn't be.

189
00:15:06,839 --> 00:15:09,808
Why? I can handle it
myself, okay?

190
00:15:11,744 --> 00:15:14,338
Can you hear me?

191
00:15:14,413 --> 00:15:15,675
Good evening.

192
00:15:15,748 --> 00:15:18,945
Uh...the Mayor
isn't here, yet.

193
00:15:19,018 --> 00:15:21,543
So I think
I'll just get started.

194
00:15:23,355 --> 00:15:25,755
I wanna thank all of you
for coming out tonight.

195
00:15:25,825 --> 00:15:29,022
I know many of you are busy
getting ready
for the tourist season,

196
00:15:29,095 --> 00:15:33,498
so... I'll just cut
to the chase.

197
00:15:33,566 --> 00:15:36,501
Yesterday, as some of you
already know,

198
00:15:36,569 --> 00:15:39,800
there was a bear attack
up on Echo Mountain.

199
00:15:39,872 --> 00:15:42,397
Unfortunately,
three men were killed

200
00:15:42,475 --> 00:15:44,705
and a fourth
was very, very lucky.

201
00:15:44,777 --> 00:15:46,768
Taku He has returned.

202
00:15:46,846 --> 00:15:49,679
Ed Janzer was found
by ranger Eagleheart

203
00:15:49,748 --> 00:15:53,115
who happened to be
in the area of the attack.
[door closes]

204
00:15:53,185 --> 00:15:55,653
Mr. Mayor.

205
00:15:55,721 --> 00:15:58,315
And brought back
to town.

206
00:15:58,390 --> 00:16:03,828
Ed was shaken up pretty badly,
but I'm happy to report
he's going to be alright.

207
00:16:03,896 --> 00:16:07,730
I've contacted
the Federal Game Warden.

208
00:16:07,800 --> 00:16:09,825
They have a couple
of Karelian bear dogs

209
00:16:09,902 --> 00:16:12,234
who'll track the animal down
and kill it.

210
00:16:12,304 --> 00:16:15,569
The problem is
they're over in Montana
right now

211
00:16:15,641 --> 00:16:17,973
and won't be able
to get here for a few days.

212
00:16:18,043 --> 00:16:20,034
I think you'll see
after looking it over

213
00:16:20,112 --> 00:16:22,376
we really don't have much
to worry about.

214
00:16:22,448 --> 00:16:25,542
Not much to worry about?
Sheriff, what about the tourists?

215
00:16:25,618 --> 00:16:29,918
I'm sure the Mayor
will wanna comment on that but, uh,

216
00:16:29,989 --> 00:16:32,981
my concern is for your safety
and the safety of our visitors.

217
00:16:33,058 --> 00:16:35,822
What are we supposed to do
in the mean time, stay inside?

218
00:16:35,895 --> 00:16:37,419
(Kassel)
No.

219
00:16:37,496 --> 00:16:40,260
For what it's worth,
those men were up there illegally

220
00:16:40,332 --> 00:16:42,664
and probably got between
the saw and her cubs.

221
00:16:42,735 --> 00:16:44,828
If they go up there
and shoot that bear,

222
00:16:44,904 --> 00:16:46,895
then the press
is gonna come up here.

223
00:16:46,972 --> 00:16:51,204
We sure as hell don't need
any one dredging up ridiculous
monster stories again.

224
00:16:51,277 --> 00:16:54,610
Exactly. That's why
there isn't going to be
any press coverage.

225
00:16:54,680 --> 00:16:57,148
Our town needs
those tourism dollars.

226
00:16:57,216 --> 00:17:00,515
How the bear's handled
is our business.
The important thing for us

227
00:17:00,586 --> 00:17:03,146
is you just keep doing
what we've done for years.

228
00:17:03,222 --> 00:17:07,090
We can't let
misguided reporters and crazy rumors

229
00:17:07,159 --> 00:17:08,854
ruin our good town.

230
00:17:08,928 --> 00:17:11,328
(Jenny )
Why do they have
to kill the bear?

231
00:17:11,397 --> 00:17:15,060
When a bear kills a human,
they usually destroy it.

232
00:17:15,134 --> 00:17:16,931
Would you kill it?

233
00:17:17,002 --> 00:17:19,238
Me? No.

234
00:17:19,405 --> 00:17:21,965
You gonna take
that shot or what?

235
00:17:24,210 --> 00:17:27,270
Here's 20.
Says you gonna scratch again.

236
00:17:27,346 --> 00:17:31,612
I can't believe you boys
are in here playing pool
and bullshitting

237
00:17:31,684 --> 00:17:34,414
when your buddies
are rotting up on that mountain,

238
00:17:34,486 --> 00:17:37,944
'cause of some pied-face
park ranger.

239
00:17:38,023 --> 00:17:44,121
The way we hear
was that that Indian saved your heart.

