Jenny, it's gonna smell me.

980
01:05:53,883 --> 01:05:55,077
[whispering]
What?

981
01:05:55,151 --> 01:05:59,110
It's gonna smell me.
I've got my period.

982
01:06:00,423 --> 01:06:02,618
That's the least
of our problems, okay?

983
01:06:02,692 --> 01:06:05,752
[whispering]
We have to wait
for the guys.

984
01:06:05,828 --> 01:06:08,558
We're gonna die out here.
I know it, I know it.

985
01:06:08,631 --> 01:06:13,762
[whispering]
No, we're not
gonna die out there.

986
01:06:28,117 --> 01:06:30,551
Thought I told you
to tie him up.

987
01:06:36,659 --> 01:06:40,595
[grunting]

988
01:06:40,663 --> 01:06:41,687
Did you hear that?

989
01:06:43,666 --> 01:06:46,294
(Tom )
Not like an animal
I've ever heard.

990
01:06:46,369 --> 01:06:48,064
(Manny )
And human neither.

991
01:06:48,137 --> 01:06:50,037
You both shut up
and listen.

992
01:06:51,040 --> 01:06:53,031
Manny, give me
my gun.

993
01:06:54,710 --> 01:06:55,836
What you're gonna do?

994
01:06:55,912 --> 01:06:59,040
I said just to pass it.

995
01:06:59,115 --> 01:07:01,379
[grunt]

996
01:07:04,287 --> 01:07:05,515
Save your damn ammo.

997
01:07:05,588 --> 01:07:07,351
[growl]

998
01:07:07,423 --> 01:07:09,288
I ain't dying
like Leo.

999
01:07:12,428 --> 01:07:16,455
(Ed)
Where're you going?
Hey, Tom!

1000
01:07:16,532 --> 01:07:20,764
[growling]
[Tom shouts]

1001
01:07:20,836 --> 01:07:23,031
[shouting]
[grunting]

1002
01:07:23,105 --> 01:07:24,436
Tom!

1003
01:07:32,548 --> 01:07:33,913
(Manny)
Tom?

1004
01:07:38,721 --> 01:07:41,246
I think I got something.

1005
01:07:44,961 --> 01:07:47,521
Oh, my God.
No!

1006
01:07:47,597 --> 01:07:49,861
Tom!
Tom.

1007
01:07:51,334 --> 01:07:53,199
Stupid fool.

1008
01:07:58,741 --> 01:08:01,869
You did this!
Huh?

1009
01:08:01,944 --> 01:08:06,005
What are you gonna do?
You gonna kill me?

1010
01:08:06,082 --> 01:08:08,516
I will, Ed.
I will.
You're the one.

1011
01:08:10,353 --> 01:08:12,014
That disappoints me, Manny.

1012
01:08:13,556 --> 01:08:15,046
All my friends are dead

1013
01:08:16,492 --> 01:08:17,891
'cause of you.

1014
01:08:19,128 --> 01:08:20,959
I'm your friend, Manny.

1015
01:08:39,615 --> 01:08:40,980
I am your friend.

1016
01:08:41,050 --> 01:08:43,245
[bang]

1017
01:08:48,624 --> 01:08:50,785
Okay.
[out of breath]

1018
01:08:50,860 --> 01:08:54,125
I don't know what happened.
We all got chased by something.

1019
01:08:54,196 --> 01:08:57,029
We all got split up.

1020
01:08:57,099 --> 01:08:58,760
I don't know
what it was.

1021
01:09:01,470 --> 01:09:04,837
Mr. Vancamp,
if you're watching this,

1022
01:09:04,907 --> 01:09:07,569
we sure as hell
better get an A for this crap.

1023
01:09:10,746 --> 01:09:13,214
I'm freezing.

1024
01:09:20,589 --> 01:09:23,080
[owl hoots]

1025
01:09:25,661 --> 01:09:27,754
What are we gonna do?

1026
01:09:28,898 --> 01:09:30,559
Just wait, I guess.

1027
01:09:31,867 --> 01:09:35,894
[loud growling]

1028
01:09:37,540 --> 01:09:39,508
Did you hear that?

1029
01:09:42,311 --> 01:09:44,279
I can't,
I cannot--

1030
01:09:44,347 --> 01:09:46,645
[whispering]
Shea, Shea,
don't go!

1031
01:09:46,716 --> 01:09:48,274
[whispering]
Shea, don't run.

1032
01:09:51,987 --> 01:09:54,251
Don't run.

1033
01:09:55,524 --> 01:09:58,322
[grunting]

1034
01:10:21,283 --> 01:10:24,218
[grunting]

1035
01:10:28,758 --> 01:10:31,522
Base One to high camp.
Base One to high camp.

1036
01:10:31,594 --> 01:10:35,860
C'mon, Johnny,
don't do this to me.
[telephone rings]

1037
01:10:35,931 --> 01:10:37,455
Sheriff's office.

1038
01:10:37,533 --> 01:10:39,728
<i>(woman)</i>
<i>I wanna know if that</i>
<i>grizzly's been killed.</i>

1039
01:10:39,802 --> 01:10:42,236
No, ma'am, the bear
hasn't been killed, yet.

1040
01:10:42,304 --> 01:10:44,169
<i>(woman)</i>
<i>Get out there</i>
<i>and skin it.</i>

1041
01:10:44,240 --> 01:10:45,832
I sure will, ma'am.

1042
01:10:45,908 --> 01:10:48,706
I'll do that
on my way to hell.

1043
01:10:48,778 --> 01:10:51,008
Yes, ma'am.
You, too.

1044
01:10:54,750 --> 01:10:56,308
[knocking at the door]

1045
01:10:56,385 --> 01:10:57,977
I'll be right there.

1046
01:10:59,121 --> 01:11:02,682
Kill the bear.
Kill the Mayor.

1047
01:11:05,795 --> 01:11:08,992
Now, save the bear.
Kill the Mayor.

1048
01:11:43,933 --> 01:11:47,835
[roll of thunder]

1049
01:11:54,143 --> 01:11:57,943
[thriller music]

1050
01:12:19,235 --> 01:12:21,100
Who the hell are you?

1051
01:12:22,671 --> 01:12:25,640
Jenny Ackers.
Thank God.
You've gotta help me.

1052
01:12:25,708 --> 01:12:28,302
Can you please help me?
I don't know
where I'm going.

1053
01:12:28,377 --> 01:12:31,574
I'm lost.
My friends are lost.
I don't know where they are.

1054
01:12:31,647 --> 01:12:33,342
Please, help me.

1055
01:12:35,651 --> 01:12:37,175
I'll help you.

1056
01:12:37,253 --> 01:12:40,484
[shouts]

1057
01:12:40,556 --> 01:12:43,218
[shouting]
Shut up!

1058
01:12:43,292 --> 01:12:46,420
Eagleheart!
Eagleheart!

1059
01:12:46,495 --> 01:12:49,293
I'm gonna kill
this girl!

1060
01:12:49,365 --> 01:12:51,299
<i>(Ed)</i>
<i>Eagleheart!</i>

1061
01:12:51,367 --> 01:12:54,495
[roll of thunder]

1062
01:13:09,118 --> 01:13:11,086
Eagleheart!

1063
01:13:11,153 --> 01:13:14,088
I know you're around here.
I can smell you.

1064
01:13:14,156 --> 01:13:15,555
[cries in pain]

1065
01:13:15,624 --> 01:13:18,957
[grunting]

1066
01:13:19,028 --> 01:13:21,189
<i>( Eagleheart)</i>
<i>Let her go!</i>

1067
01:13:26,068 --> 01:13:28,832
Let her go.

1068
01:13:28,904 --> 01:13:31,338
You must think
I'm dumb as dirt.

1069
01:13:33,509 --> 01:13:35,272
I'm the one you want.

1070
01:13:36,912 --> 01:13:39,779
See, that's the difference
between you and me.

1071
01:13:42,718 --> 01:13:45,619
I'm willing to kill
for what I believe in.

1072
01:13:47,056 --> 01:13:51,356
[loud growling]

1073
01:13:58,467 --> 01:14:00,901
[distant bang]

1074
01:14:10,479 --> 01:14:12,037
(Jay)
Sheriff!

1075
01:14:12,114 --> 01:14:13,479
Thank God.

1076
01:14:13,549 --> 01:14:15,983
What the hell
is going on up here?

1077
01:14:16,051 --> 01:14:19,043
[out of breath]
We've got friends up there.
They're in trouble.

1078
01:14:19,121 --> 01:14:22,420
You, come with me.
You, in the car.

1079
01:14:22,491 --> 01:14:24,459
Here.
I'll take that.

1080
01:14:25,894 --> 01:14:27,589
Get up!

1081
01:14:27,663 --> 01:14:30,860
[cries in pain]

1082
01:14:30,933 --> 01:14:32,491
Stop!

1083
01:14:32,568 --> 01:14:35,401
Are you gonna play
the hero now, kid?

1084
01:14:39,942 --> 01:14:41,500
I know that gun.

1085
01:14:41,577 --> 01:14:43,670
(Ed)
That's a nice gun,

1086
01:14:43,746 --> 01:14:45,475
specially when it's loaded.

1087
01:14:48,283 --> 01:14:51,343
[bang]

1088
01:14:57,493 --> 01:14:59,688
Wait up!

1089
01:15:12,808 --> 01:15:16,005
He'll be okay.
Are you okay?

1090
01:15:23,686 --> 01:15:27,349
[low grunt]

1091
01:15:28,957 --> 01:15:30,083
Are you guys alright?

1092
01:15:30,159 --> 01:15:31,183
(Rich)
Yeah.

1093
01:15:31,260 --> 01:15:32,818
Oh!

1094
01:15:32,895 --> 01:15:35,261
(Jay)
What happened?
Is he gonna be alright?

1095
01:15:35,330 --> 01:15:36,695
Yeah, he's good.

1096
01:15:38,200 --> 01:15:40,794
You'll be okay.
Okay, John?

1097
01:15:40,869 --> 01:15:43,565
Richard, Richard,

1098
01:15:43,639 --> 01:15:47,075
tha--tha--tha--
that's not a bear.

1099
01:15:47,142 --> 01:15:51,806
[loud growling]

1100
01:15:51,880 --> 01:15:58,444
[grunting]

1101
01:16:00,055 --> 01:16:01,386
No way.

1102
01:16:01,457 --> 01:16:03,584
Look at that.

1103
01:16:03,659 --> 01:16:08,460
Oh, my God!
It's freaking huge.

1104
01:16:10,099 --> 01:16:11,896
<i>(Kassel)</i>
<i>Where is everybody?</i>

1105
01:16:11,967 --> 01:16:14,561
Sheriff, over here!

1106
01:16:17,406 --> 01:16:19,840
(Jay)
Where did he--
Where did he go?

1107
01:16:33,355 --> 01:16:35,220
[thumping]

1108
01:16:35,290 --> 01:16:38,817
[all laugh]
[thumping]

1109
01:16:38,894 --> 01:16:41,954
There's gotta be
something wrong
with the TV, Mr. Vancamp.

1110
01:16:42,030 --> 01:16:44,055
We've been watching
this tape all weekend.

1111
01:16:44,133 --> 01:16:47,625
I had this incredible footage
of the grizzly bear.
He was like that.

1112
01:16:47,703 --> 01:16:50,433
Except if you're standing up
and he'll roar!

1113
01:16:52,040 --> 01:16:53,166
Roaring?

1114
01:16:53,242 --> 01:16:54,266
(Jay)
I'm serious.

1115
01:16:54,343 --> 01:16:56,243
(Vancamp)
I'm sure you did, Jay.

1116
01:16:56,311 --> 01:16:58,541
Big surprise
for all of us, huh?

1117
01:16:58,614 --> 01:17:01,139
Lucky for you
Richard got some nice photos.

1118
01:17:01,216 --> 01:17:04,583
Actually, uhm,
Jay took these.

1119
01:17:04,653 --> 01:17:06,553
(Vancamp)
Jay took these?

1120
01:17:06,622 --> 01:17:08,180
(Rich)
Yeah.
I did the research

1121
01:17:08,257 --> 01:17:10,555
in the library, mostly.

1122
01:17:10,626 --> 01:17:12,150
(Vancamp)
Let's see.

1123
01:17:12,227 --> 01:17:14,787
These are good!

1124
01:17:14,863 --> 01:17:17,297
Looks like you got
precariously close there.

1125
01:17:17,366 --> 01:17:18,731
[all laugh]

1126
01:17:18,801 --> 01:17:22,999
And this is
the killer bear, huh?

1127
01:17:23,071 --> 01:17:27,838
(Vancamp )
I thought you understood
when I said in-depth.

1128
01:17:27,910 --> 01:17:33,439
That I wanted something
a bit more... in-depth.

1129
01:17:33,515 --> 01:17:36,040
What we have here
is a little thin,
don't you think?

1130
01:17:36,118 --> 01:17:39,485
No, I don't think.
I don't understand why
every time I do a project,

1131
01:17:39,555 --> 01:17:41,216
you gotta give me
so much sh--

1132
01:17:41,290 --> 01:17:45,522
Excuse me, but I think
if you look at the research
that we actually did

1133
01:17:45,594 --> 01:17:51,760
in it's entirety,
you'll see that we went
the extra mile, and that's him.

1134
01:17:51,834 --> 01:17:58,262
Well, where might I find
this extravaganza.

1135
01:17:58,340 --> 01:18:03,903
Well, it would be
extravagantly laid out
in your extravagant office.

1136
01:18:18,727 --> 01:18:21,389
<i>(anchorwoman)</i>
<i>Earlier today,</i>
<i>this amateur video</i>

1137
01:18:21,463 --> 01:18:24,193
<i>created quite a stir</i>
<i>amongst some local residents.</i>

1138
01:18:24,266 --> 01:18:28,464
<i>A Pine Creek man claims</i>
<i>this supposed Bigfoot creature</i>
<i>pictured here</i>

1139
01:18:28,537 --> 01:18:31,529
<i>was responsible</i>
<i>for the recent deaths</i>
<i>of several local men.</i>

1140
01:18:31,607 --> 01:18:33,302
<i>Family members</i>
<i>of the deceased</i>

1141
01:18:33,375 --> 01:18:36,867
<i>responded by calling the video</i>
<i>a sick joke.</i>

1142
01:18:36,945 --> 01:18:39,311
<i>Local experts</i>
<i>have deemed the tape</i>
<i>a hoax,</i>

1143
01:18:39,381 --> 01:18:43,442
<i>denouncing the grainy footage</i>
<i>is nothing more than a man</i>
<i>in a monkey suit.</i>

1144
01:18:43,518 --> 01:18:46,214
<i>The man behind the film,</i>
<i>Dennis Vancamp,</i>

1145
01:18:46,288 --> 01:18:48,779
<i>is a science teacher</i>
<i>at Pine Creek High School.</i>

1146
01:18:48,857 --> 01:18:50,324
<i>The Mayor had this to say.</i>

1147
01:18:50,392 --> 01:18:56,228
<i>I can't tell you</i>
<i>how ashamed I feel today.</i>

1148
01:18:56,298 --> 01:18:58,266
<i>I say, as a community,</i>

1149
01:18:58,333 --> 01:19:04,135
<i>we will not and cannot tolerate</i>
<i>such unacceptable forms</i>
<i>of behavior</i>

1150
01:19:04,206 --> 01:19:08,370
<i>among those who serve</i>
<i>as role models</i>
<i>for our children.</i>

1151
01:19:08,443 --> 01:19:10,775
<i>The truth must overcome.</i>

1152
01:19:10,846 --> 01:19:13,246
<i>(anchorwoman)</i>
<i>Next up, Captain Jimbo</i>

1153
01:19:13,315 --> 01:19:15,749
<i>gives us his five-day</i>
<i>micro planet.</i>

1154
01:19:22,157 --> 01:19:25,058
[loud cricket chirping]

1155
01:19:25,127 --> 01:19:29,530
<i>(male narrator)</i>
<i>Sometimes,</i>
<i>in the deep woods</i>

1156
01:19:29,598 --> 01:19:32,465
<i>when the mountain is lone,</i>

1157
01:19:32,534 --> 01:19:36,129
<i>when the sun no longer</i>
<i>touches my face</i>

1158
01:19:36,204 --> 01:19:39,230
<i>and the creatures lay still,</i>

1159
01:19:39,308 --> 01:19:44,075
<i>I can feel in there</i>
<i>Taku He.</i>

1160
01:19:46,715 --> 01:19:48,706
<i>Taku He.</i>

1161
01:19:52,821 --> 01:19:55,517
<i>Taku He.</i>

1162
01:19:57,192 --> 01:20:01,288
[loud growling]

1163
01:20:01,363 --> 01:20:02,297
<i>Taku He.</i>

1164
01:20:02,299 --> 01:20:03,161
<i>Taku He.</i>

1165
01:20:03,231 --> 01:20:06,064
[growling]